<title>ITALY: Italy's Milan sees August CPI at 4.0 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Italy's Milan sees August CPI at 4.0 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>MILAN 1996-08-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Milan said its August consumer price index was unchanged month-on-month and 4.0 percent higher year-on-year.</p>
<p>In July, Milan's inflation rate was 0.0 percent and 4.4 percent respectively.</p>
<p>Milan is the first of 10 Italian cities publishing the inflation data over the next two days.</p>
<p>The city's CPI has a weighting of 19.09 percent on the national index. The 10 sample cities have a combined weighting of 69.67 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>Following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to July 1996):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.0    (0.0)    4.0  (4.4)</p>
<p>    Food				 -0.2   (-0.2)    4.5  (4.8)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.0    (0.0)    5.0  (5.0)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   0.3   (-0.4)    8.5  (8.2)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.0    (0.0)    3.4  (4.4)</p>
<p>    Health services		   0.0   (-0.3)    2.1  (2.0)</p>
<p>    Transportation		    0.2   (0.4)     4.4  (5.2)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture     0.4   (-0.3)    1.9  (2.3)</p>
<p>    Education			   0.1    (0.0)    4.7  (4.6)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.0    (0.1)    4.1  (4.3)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	 0.0    (0.0)    2.2  (2.2)</p>
<p>-- Milan newsroom ++392 66129526</p>
